trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> module to create a regression model that can predict values for a specified number of quantiles.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> module to create a regression model that can predict values for a specified number of quantiles.

trans-unit.source: Quantile regression is useful if you want to understand more about the distribution of the predicted value, rather than get a single mean prediction value.
trans-unit.target: Quantile regression is useful if you want to understand more about the distribution of the predicted value, rather than get a single mean prediction value.

trans-unit.source: This method has many applications, including:
trans-unit.target: This method has many applications, including:

trans-unit.source: Predicting prices
trans-unit.target: Predicting prices

trans-unit.source: Estimating student performance or applying growth charts to assess child development
trans-unit.target: Estimating student performance or applying growth charts to assess child development

trans-unit.source: Discovering predictive relationships in cases where there is only a weak relationship between variables
trans-unit.target: Discovering predictive relationships in cases where there is only a weak relationship between variables

trans-unit.source: This regression method is a supervised learning method, and therefore requires a <newTerm>tagged dataset</newTerm>, which includes a label column.
trans-unit.target: This regression method is a supervised learning method, and therefore requires a <newTerm>tagged dataset</newTerm>, which includes a label column.

trans-unit.source: The label column must contain numerical values.
trans-unit.target: The label column must contain numerical values.

trans-unit.source: You can train the model by providing the model and the tagged dataset as an input to <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> or <link xlink:href="038d91b6-c2f2-42a1-9215-1f2c20ed1b40" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Sweep Parameters</link>.
trans-unit.target: You can train the model by providing the model and the tagged dataset as an input to <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> or <link xlink:href="038d91b6-c2f2-42a1-9215-1f2c20ed1b40" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Sweep Parameters</link>.

trans-unit.source: The trained model can then be used to predict values for the new input examples.
trans-unit.target: The trained model can then be used to predict values for the new input examples.

trans-unit.source: Understanding Quantile Regression
trans-unit.target: Understanding Quantile Regression

trans-unit.source: There are many different types of regression.
trans-unit.target: There are many different types of regression.

trans-unit.source: In the most basic sense, regression means fitting a model to a target expressed as a numeric vector.
trans-unit.target: In the most basic sense, regression means fitting a model to a target expressed as a numeric vector.

trans-unit.source: However, statisticians have been developing increasingly advanced methods for regression.
trans-unit.target: However, statisticians have been developing increasingly advanced methods for regression.

trans-unit.source: The simplest definition of quantile is a value that divides a set of data into equal-sized groups, and the quantile values mark the boundaries between groups.
trans-unit.target: The simplest definition of quantile is a value that divides a set of data into equal-sized groups, and the quantile values mark the boundaries between groups.

trans-unit.source: Statistically, quantiles are values taken at regular intervals from the inverse of the cumulative distribution function (CDF) of a random variable.
trans-unit.target: Statistically, quantiles are values taken at regular intervals from the inverse of the cumulative distribution function (CDF) of a random variable.

trans-unit.source: <newTerm>Quantile regression</newTerm> is used if you want to understand more about the distribution of the predicted value.
trans-unit.target: <newTerm>Quantile regression</newTerm> is used if you want to understand more about the distribution of the predicted value.

trans-unit.source: Whereas linear regression models attempt to predict the value of a numeric variable using instead of a single estimate, the <newTerm>mean</newTerm>, sometimes you need to predict the range or entire distribution of the target variable.
trans-unit.target: Whereas linear regression models attempt to predict the value of a numeric variable using instead of a single estimate, the <newTerm>mean</newTerm>, sometimes you need to predict the range or entire distribution of the target variable.

trans-unit.source: To do this, you can use techniques such as Bayesian regression and quantile regression.
trans-unit.target: To do this, you can use techniques such as Bayesian regression and quantile regression.

trans-unit.source: Tree-based quantile regression models, such as the one used in this module, have the additional advantage that they can be used to predict non-parametric distributions.
trans-unit.target: Tree-based quantile regression models, such as the one used in this module, have the additional advantage that they can be used to predict non-parametric distributions.

trans-unit.source: How to Configure a Quantile Regression Model
trans-unit.target: How to Configure a Quantile Regression Model

trans-unit.source: Specify how you want the model to be trained, by setting the <ui>Create trainer mode</ui> option.
trans-unit.target: Specify how you want the model to be trained, by setting the <ui>Create trainer mode</ui> option.

trans-unit.source: When you create this model, you have two options for training the model: using a single set of parameters with <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link>, or choosing a range of parameters and training the model with a parameter sweep.

trans-unit.source: Technical Notes
trans-unit.target: Technical Notes

trans-unit.source: The <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> module in Azure Machine Learning is an implementation of random forest quantile regression using decision trees.
trans-unit.target: The <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> module in Azure Machine Learning is an implementation of random forest quantile regression using decision trees.

trans-unit.source: Random forests can be helpful to avoid overfitting that can occur with decision trees.
trans-unit.target: Random forests can be helpful to avoid overfitting that can occur with decision trees.

trans-unit.source: A decision tree is a binary tree-like flow chart, where at every interior node, one decides which of the two child nodes to continue to, based on the value of one of the features of the input.
trans-unit.target: A decision tree is a binary tree-like flow chart, where at every interior node, one decides which of the two child nodes to continue to, based on the value of one of the features of the input.

trans-unit.source: In each leaf node, a value is returned.
trans-unit.target: In each leaf node, a value is returned.

trans-unit.source: In the interior nodes, the decision is based on the test <math>x≤v</math>, where <math>x</math> is the value of the feature in the input sample and <math>v</math> is one of the possible values of this feature.
trans-unit.target: In the interior nodes, the decision is based on the test <math>x≤v</math>, where <math>x</math> is the value of the feature in the input sample and <math>v</math> is one of the possible values of this feature.

trans-unit.source: The functions that can be produced by a regression tree are all the piece-wise constant functions.
trans-unit.target: The functions that can be produced by a regression tree are all the piece-wise constant functions.

trans-unit.source: In a random forest, an ensemble of trees is created by using bagging to select a subset of random samples and features of the train data, and then fit a decision tree to each subset of data.
trans-unit.target: In a random forest, an ensemble of trees is created by using bagging to select a subset of random samples and features of the train data, and then fit a decision tree to each subset of data.

trans-unit.source: Unlike the random forest algorithm, which averages out the output of the all the trees, <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> keeps all the predicted labels in trees specified by the parameter <ui>Quantile sample count</ui> and outputs the distribution, so that the user can view the quantile values for the given instance.
trans-unit.target: Unlike the random forest algorithm, which averages out the output of the all the trees, <ui>Fast Forest Quantile Regression</ui> keeps all the predicted labels in trees specified by the parameter <ui>Quantile sample count</ui> and outputs the distribution, so that the user can view the quantile values for the given instance.
